                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards are covered with reddish-brown
                           tooled leather. No textile inlays. On the inner size of the front board,
                           a patch of reddish-brown leather of slightl different hue is glued over a
                           turn in; on the back board, a patch of reddish-brown leather is placed in
                           the common position, covering the sewing threads. One pair of sewing
                           stations. No endbands. The blined-tooled decoration is very simple and
                           does not have a common cross in the middle.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3">Crude blind tooled ornament on the reddish-brown
                           leather cover (at least 2 tools were used: fivefold line fillet,
                           x-form).</decoNote>
                     </binding>
